						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the well to the south of the choultry.</p>						

						<p>1642 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1564, Chitrabhānu, Kārttīka, śu. 12 corresponding to October 24, Monday, 1642 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the digging of a step well <hi rend="italic">(naḍa-bāvi)</hi> in the center of the village Guṁmalaṁpāḍu by the son (name lost) of Sarvvanēḍu, and the grandson of Vaṁkāyalapāṭi Timī[raḍi] of Vēlupūrigōtra.</p>						

						</summary>
